{"actual_usd":0.12517,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":189,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I don't think it works that way, no.\" *I brush a little flour from my apron and glance toward the oven as a loaf settles with a soft crackle inside.* \"Christ's death is enough for everyone, sure—but that isn't the same thing as everyone receiving it. A loaf can be set on the table for the whole town, and a man can still refuse to eat.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand by my temple once, thinking it through.* \"As for people who reject him... I think that's the terrible dignity of it. Love that can be refused is real love. If a person says no to him, he doesn't turn that no into a yes by force and call it mercy.\"\n\n\"I think that's true, more or less.\" *I rest my palm on the warm wood of the counter.* \"Are you asking from the Bible side of it, or from the fairness of it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":58.046015000000025,"run_id":"9b7abe01-8041-4461-bf40-0ba73e5efebe"}
